            Title = "Vendor Catalog & Approved Vendor List (AVL)",
            Slug = "vendors-catalog-avl",
            Summary = "The Catalog tab on a vendor: the parts a vendor supplies, the Approved (AVL) and Preferred Source flags, bulk CSV import, and how it ties into purchasing.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 6,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 6,
            AppRoutes = """["/vendors"]""",
            Tags = """["vendors","catalog","avl","procurement","vendor-parts"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Vendor Catalog & Approved Vendor List (AVL)\n\nEvery vendor detail panel has a **Catalog** tab. This is where you record the **parts a vendor supplies** — the vendor-part relationship that links a Part in your catalog to a Vendor, with vendor-scoped sourcing details. It is the supply side of the same data you see on a Part's **Sources** tab; the Catalog tab just looks at it from the vendor's point of view (\"what does *this vendor* sell us?\").\n\n### Opening the Catalog tab\n\nFrom the Vendors list, click a vendor row to open its detail panel, then click the **Catalog** tab (next to Info, Purchase Orders, and Scorecard). The tab loads the list of vendor-parts for that vendor.\n\n### What a vendor-part row holds\n\nEach catalog row is one part this vendor can supply, with vendor-specific fields:\n\n- **Part** — the part number and name from your Parts catalog.\n- **Vendor Part Number** — the vendor's own SKU / catalog number for the part.\n- **Vendor MPN** — the manufacturer part number when the vendor is a distributor reselling someone else's part (distinct from the part's own engineering MPN).\n- **Lead Time (days)**, **Min Order Qty (MOQ)**, **Pack Size** — vendor-scoped procurement parameters.\n- **Country of Origin** and **HTS Code** — trade-compliance fields.\n- **Price tiers** — quantity-break pricing (covered in the *Managing Vendor Pricing* module).\n- **Approved** and **Preferred** flags — see below.\n- **Notes** and **Last Quoted Date**.\n\n### The Approved flag (AVL)\n\nThe **Approved** switch is your **Approved Vendor List (AVL)** marker. An approved row means \"this vendor is cleared to supply this part\" — it has passed whatever qualification your shop requires. Approved rows show a green check; un-approved rows show a blocked icon. Purchasing uses this to steer buyers toward qualified sources.\n\n### The Preferred Source flag\n\nThe **Preferred** switch marks the *go-to* source for a part, shown with a filled star you can toggle right from the list. A part can have only **one preferred source at a time** — marking one vendor as preferred automatically clears it on every other vendor for that part, so there's always exactly one answer. The preferred vendor's lead time, minimum order quantity, and pack size are the ones reordering and auto-generated purchase orders use.\n\n### Adding, editing, and removing catalog entries\n\n- **+ Add** opens the vendor-part form dialog. The vendor is locked (you're already inside that vendor), so you pick the **Part** and fill in the vendor-scoped fields, including the Approved and Preferred toggles.\n- The **edit** (pencil) row action reopens the same form to change any field.\n- The **delete** (trash) row action removes the part from this vendor's catalog. This unlinks the vendor-part relationship; it does not delete the Part itself.\n- The **Is Manufacturer** switch on the form tells the system whether the vendor *is* the manufacturer (so the manufacturer is the vendor and you enter one part number) or a distributor reselling someone else's part (where you record both the vendor's part number and the original manufacturer's part number).\n\n### Bulk import\n\nTo bring in a distributor's catalog or a long price list, use **Import** at the top of the Catalog tab. It works in two steps:\n\n1. **Pick a file** — drag in or browse for a spreadsheet file. A **Download template** link gives you the exact columns to use.\n2. **Preview** — the system reads the file and marks every row **Add**, **Update**, or **Error**, with a running count. Rows with a problem show an error message, and the **Apply** button stays grayed out until you fix them and re-import.\n\nApplying saves all the adds and updates at once. Import matches on part number, so parts the vendor already lists are updated rather than duplicated.\n\n### How the catalog feeds purchasing\n\nThe catalog is core reference data that the rest of purchasing reads:\n\n- **Reordering and auto-generated purchase orders** look at your preferred source and its lead time, minimum order quantity, and pricing to suggest what to buy.\n- **Purchase orders** pull the vendor's part number and price when you add a part this vendor supplies.\n- The **Approved flag** keeps buyers ordering from qualified sources.\n\nBecause it's shared reference data, any change to a catalog entry is recorded on **both** the vendor's and the part's activity logs.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        // ── Vendor Catalog — Guided Tour (Walkthrough) ───────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
